	<div style="position: relative; top: 6px; left:5px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 13px; padding-left: 45px;">How does Magelo Update collect information?</div>	
	<div style="position: relative; top: 6px; left:10px;">
		<img class="png32" style="position: absolute; top:0px; left:0px;" src="/images/shared/right_menu/support_icone_off.png" width="33" height="15">
		<img class="png32" style="position: absolute;top:-17px; left:4px;" src="/images/localized/picto/faq_icone.png" width="24" height="24">
	</div>
	<hr class="line">
	<br>
	
	
	<div>Your computer communicates with the game servers and receives relevant character data - some data is kept serverside, but most character data is transmitted to your machine. Bank, inventory, you name it, you got it local. Your machine places the data in parts of your computer memory. <br/>
<br/>
<a href='http://www.testmagelo.com/magelo_update.jspa' target='new'>Magelo Update</a> doesn&#039;t sniff the packet stream, which would violate the EULA (End User License Agreement). What it does is read the relevant memory locations. The data is always placed in the same spots or at least with the same markers, so it knows where to look. Furthermore, it is direct data. Nothing is decoded or interpreted. Item and character data are not encrypted so no decryption is necessary. In-game memory is only read, never written to. Magelo Update does not change your in-game experiences. <br/>
<br/>
When you log into the game Magelo Update reads the relevant memory locations and compiles a list of item and character information. It checks Magelo&#039;s central database to see if anything is new or changed. If so, it transmits updates to the database. <br/>
<br/>
Thereafter, every time you enter a zone, Magelo Update reads memory and checks its item and character tables for changes. If it finds anything new and/or changed, it transmits updates to the central Magelo database. (In practice, very little processing is needed to do this. The little program is asleep otherwise.) <br/>
<br/>
Note that Magelo Update&#039;s main mission is to update the central Magelo database. In this way everyone benefits. <br/>
<blockquote class="blockquote"><em class="emphasis">Written initially by <a href='http://www.valoran.net/' target='new'>Onetree</a></em></blockquote></div>
